      "content": "The school's approach is framed as the standard because it aligns with modern, progressive educational philosophy which prioritizes social equity and psychological safety for all students. Labeling parental concerns as merely \"traditional\" is a way of framing them as outdated when they conflict with established principles of modern diversity and inclusion. This framing is not neutral; it reflects a deliberate institutional choice to uphold a specific social value—acceptance—over differing personal beliefs.",
